  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>reduction in ventricular tachyarrhythmias events</measure>
    <time_frame>3 months</time_frame>
    <description>Using careful clinical monitoring, we will compare the burden of VT/VF after ablation (including FIRM) to the burden preceding ablation.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>safety of ventricular basket mapping in patients undergoing ablation</measure>
    <time_frame>1 month</time_frame>
    <description>To assess the incidence of adverse events arising from ablation using basket mapping in the ventricles. These include but are not limited to stroke, systemic thromboembolism, MI or acute coronary syndrome, groin complications, or death.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
